               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_5-item1">
                     <author key="person_f3341">
                        <persName type="supplied" subtype="aut">Psuedo Palladiusمنسوب إلى فلاذيوس</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_7755">Commentary on the Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7755">شرح فصول أبقراط المنسوب إلى فلاذيوس</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Maʿhad al-turāṯ alʿilmī al-ʿarābī.</note>
                     <note>The front matter attributes the text to <persName type="Standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/40170779" key="person_40170779">Palladius (fl. C. <date calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="0500" notAfter="0599" cert="medium">6th century</date>)</persName> although recent scholarship contests that (see Pormann et al, 2018). It contains commentaries on the following aphorisms:: 1, 4, 9, 11, 12, 14, 16 and 17; <seg n="2">II</seg>: 1 and 2, 9, 15, 19.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <persName key="person_305306812" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/305306812">Biesterfeldt, Hinrich</persName>, <title level="a">Palladius on the Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>, <title level="m">The Libraries of the Neoplatonists</title>
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="2007" notAfter="2007">2007</date>, <biblScope unit="pages">pp. 385-397</biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
